    <h1>Chess</h1>
    <p id="chess-p">Chess is a popular board game that is played almost everywhere in the world. It is played both casually and competitively. There are many formats of chess, many of which are based around the timer</p>
    <h3>How to play</h3>
    <p id="chess-p">There are many rules in chess and a couple of win conditions</p>
    <ul>
      <li id="main-li"><strong>Basic Rules</strong></li>
      <li>
        <ul>
          <li>Chess is a game played by 2 players</li>
          <li>One player controls the white pieces while the other controls the black pieces</li>
          <li>The person who controls the white pieces moves first</li>
          <li>A person is required to move one piece on their turn</li>
          <li>A player may remove one of their opponent's pieces if one of their pieces are able to do so</li>
          <li>
            <ul>
              <li>This is called a capture</li>
            </ul>
            </li>
          <li>The game ends when one of the player's have reached a win condition</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li id="main-li"><strong>Win Conditions</strong></li>
      <li>
        <ul>
          <li>If a player checkmates their opponent, the player wins the game</li>
          <li>
            <ul>
              <li>A checkmate is accomplished by putting the opposing player's king in a position where not only is the king can be captured in one move but also where the player can't do anything to prevent the capture</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>If a timer is being used a player runs out of time, they lose the game</li>
          <li>If a player forfeits they lose the game</li>
          <li>A draw can occur if both players agree to a draw</li>
          <li>A draw can also occur if both players repeat the exact same set of moves three times in a row</li>
         <li>A draw can also occur if a player is unable to make any move</li>
       </ul>
     </li>
      <li id="main-li"><strong>Chess Pieces</strong></li>
     <li>
       <ul>
         <li>There are 6 different types of pieces in the game</li>
         <li>Pawn</li>
         <li>
           <ul>
             <li>The pawn can move up to one space forward per turn</li>
             <li>If it is the first time the pawn is moving, the pawn may move 2 spaces forward</li>
             <li>A pawn can capture an opposing player's piece by moving one space diagonally if there is an opponent's piece there</li>
           </ul>
         </li>
         <li>Rook</li>
         <li>
           <ul>
             <li>A rook can move any number of spaces horizontally and vertically as long as the rook isn't being blocked by another piece</li>
             <li>A rook can capture any piece that is horizontal or vertical to it, as long as the rook isn't being blocked by another piece</li>
           </ul>
         </li>
         <li>Bishop</li>
         <li>
           <ul>
             <li>A bishop can move any number of spaces diagonally</li>
             <li>It can can capture an opposing player's space similarly as the rook except in the diagonal direction</li>
           </ul>
         </li>
         <li>Knight</li>
         <li>
           <ul>
             <li>The knight can move 2 spaces horizontally or vertically but it also must move 1 space perpendicular to the direction that the knight moved 2 spaces towards</li>
             <li>The knight can't be blocked by other pieces as the knight can, in a way, jump over pieces</li>
             <li>The knight can capture a piece that is in a position where the knight can move</li>
           </ul>
         </li>
         <li>Queen</li>
         <li>
           <ul>
             <li>The Queen is a combination of the bishop and rook as it can move in any direction that a rook and bishop could</li>
             <li>Likewise, the queen can capture pieces the same way a rook and bishop could</li>
           </ul>
         </li>		
         <li>King</li>
         <li>
           <ul>
             <li>The king can move one space in any direction and take a piece that is one space away from it</li>
           </ul>
         </li>
       </ul>
     </li>
      <li id="main-li"><strong>Board Structure</strong></li>
     <li>
       <ul>
         <li>The board of the game consists of an 8x8 board with square tiles that alternate between 2 different colors</li>
